docs.lead_paragraph: None of the surviving sufferers from tetraethyl lead poisoning appears to be in serious danger and it is believed that the death list of five will not be increased, according to reports from Reconstruction Hospital.

headline.main: NO PERIL TO PUBLIC SEEN IN ETHYL GAS; Bureau of Mines Reports After Long Experiments With Motor Exhausts. MORE DEATHS ARE UNLIKELY All the 34-at Reconstruction Hospital Are Believed to Be Out of Danger. LITTLE USED IN THE CITY Tetra-Ethyl Compound Sold to Only Two Firms, Which Are Experimenting, Says Standard Oil.

docs.abstract: No peril to public from exhaust fumes, Bur of Mines report
docs.snippet: None of the surviving sufferers from tetraethyl lead poisoning appears to be in serious danger and it is believed that the death list of five will not be increased, according to reports from Reconstruction Hospital.
